			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">New abilities for old Mobs.<a name="47317"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jun 21 04 11:20 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Recently i've decided to start making mental notes of which particular mobs have new abilities, of which they previously did not have.  After what happened to me last night in Lower Faydark I decided to impart what I knew and to see if any other members were aware of new abilities, added to mobs which they originally did not have.
<br />

<br />
The first two examples I have are Trilcor and Fireclaw in Echo Caverns.  Fireclaw's new ability makes a lot of sense because of the Fireclaw Carapace he drops when killed.  His new ability is a 75 dmg fire sting proc if he hits you.  
<br />

<br />
However, Trilcor's is another story.  Trilcor drops nothing worth any real value yet he has a stun, dot diseased proc that occurs often.  If he hits, which is quite often, you initially take 5 dmg, then some unknown amount afterwards, while you are stunned then the effect of being stunned lasts for about 10 seconds or more.  
<br />

<br />
In order to defeat him I had to twist Selo's Consonant Chain along with my current dot.  Additionally, both Trilcor and Fireclaw now spawn in different places within Echo Caverns.  They used to only spawn in the area leading to The Deep's zone.  Sometimes they are wanderers as well.
<br />

<br />
My last example, from last night, is that of the Corrupted Brownie in Lower Faydark.  I was amazed at his new ability, which is constant and doesn't seem to be a proc.  Well after I killed the Tainted Brownie he immediately spawned, which is typical, so I began to kite him.  But then I noticed my monitor screen changing and one moment he'd be at least 6 feet away from me, the next moment i'm taking 125 dmg and he's right behind me.
<br />

<br />
Well it turns out his new ability is to cause his target to shadow step or have the same affect on them as Melanie's Mellifluous Motion.  The only difference is that he knows where you are going to temporarily port to, so he will always be there waiting to attack.  It's a good thing I was right at the Greater Faydark zone line because I was able to zone, before the porting kicked in.  
<br />

<br />
Now my only concern, other than the obvious one, is whether his new ability affects only one person or potentially an entire group.  In any case, I'd like to know if anyone else has noticed new abilities added to certain old mobs.  I can't imagine how many other named and/or quest type mobs have new abilities.    </span></td>
			</tr><tr>
