				<td colspan="2"><span><blockquote><b>Quote:</b><br><span class="quote">The only difference is that he knows where you are going to temporarily port to, so he will always be there waiting to attack.</span></blockquote>
<br />

<br />

<br />
hehehehe, sounds like you got SUMMONED!!!! Did it flash a summoned message? <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-13.gif" border="0" alt="LOL" hspace="2" />
<br />

<br />
The mob that has the ability to summon will do so every x amount of seconds after you have been out of melee range. It will place you at the same loc as the mob that summons you so it will seem like they are on top of you. Its also difficult to run away from them as they will keep summoning you.
<br />

<br />
This ability will only affect the person who is on top of the hate list and is out of melee range, IE not group wide. Also, it does not occur until you have done a trivial amount of damage to the mob that summons.
<br />

<br />
Some of the corrupteds are known to summon, some might be new, ability wise. Not sure, but I think my sk friend mentioned the corrupted fish in Kedge summons, could be my memory playing tricks. I know that the corrupted Hill Giant in RM does not summon.</span></td>
